my period is irregular does that mean i cant have babies no it doesn't nessesarily mean you can't have babies it may mean that it will be a bit harder though i've had irregular periods for years now i would go see a dr and get some tests done a few reasons for irregular periods are pcos insulin resistance and endometriosis i've had babies although it took longer than most people start trying to chart your cycle make note of any unexplained spotting or cramping that will also help your dr try and determine if there is something wrong be aggressive as well a lot of dr's at least in my experience will test for one thing and when it comes back normal leave it at that i've had to fight hard for my testing which revealed insulin resistance and pcos good luck Polycystic ovary syndrome Insulin Hormone replacement therapy (trans) Nutrition Diabetes mellitus Hypoglycemia Social rule Pitaten Pregnancy Poker jargon Anchor Chronic fatigue syndrome Extreme Programming Infertility The Beatles discography Breastfeeding Menstrual cycle Ferret Piccolo Junior Saga Growth hormone treatment Knife Supreme Power Non-Hodgkin's lymphoma 2000 Australian Grand Prix Luck USS Wahoo (SS-238) Drill bit Kender Pakistani cricket team in West Indies in 2005 Infantilism Metformin Unreal Blood on the Tracks Urinary incontinence Contract Friends Kasparov versus The World Electrophysiology Hyperprolactinaemia Thiazolidinedione Characters in the Smurfs Main characters of Fullmetal Alchemist Super Mario 128 Diablo II: Lord of Destruction Dance Dance Revolution EXTREME Abortion debate Fast bowling Leeds United F.C. Variable star Intensive insulinotherapy Appeasement Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an Normal distribution Hebrew calendar Prolactinoma Sesotho language Theory of conduct Prostate cancer Diabetic ketoacidosis Floppy disk First aid Obstetrics Tenshinhan Hall & Oates 2004 U.S. presidential election controversy, vote suppression Theodicy Nicomachean Ethics Irregular military Cardiac arrh